text: Ints is a Latvian masculine given name. It is a short form of Indriķis, the Latvian form of Henry and may refer to: * Ints Cālītis (born 1931), Latvian politician and former political prisoner * Ints Dālderis (born 1971), Latvian clarinetist and politician, Minister of Culture of Latvia * Ints Ķuzis (borh 1962), Latvian policeman, police general and former commander in-chief of Latvian Police * Ints Teterovskis (born 1972), Latvian conductor Category:Latvian masculine given names
title: Ints
